5:
There's something I'd like to ask you
about. Do you have a moment?
9:
Huh. How'd you even know I was
here?
13:
I just figured you wouldn't leave us
unattended.
15:
To be honest, I didn't think you'd do
the snooping yourself. I thought
you'd send a subordinate to do it.
19:
The Guild Knights are nothing if not
woefully understaffed.
23: What was it you wanted to ask?
27:
Tomorrow, we're going to release all
the Purgers and send them to the
surface.
31:
Whoa, whoa. Hold on. That sounds
to me more like threatening than
"asking."
35:
I do have something to ask you. But
that's not it—the part about the
Purgers is already set in stone.
38:
Remember the tears in space that
we saw in the Kaleidoscope? We
found a way to recreate those on
the surface.
40:
This time, we can make them even
bigger. Big enough that multiple
Purgers can pass through
simultaneously.
43:
That way, even people in Palpebra
will be able to see the real threat
with their own eyes.
47:
I see... Then you can prove to the
big-shots in the Guild that what
you're saying is true.
50:
While that's happening, we'll rescue
the remaining Vesta. Once we do so,
they won't have a reason to occupy
that settlement anymore.
55:
You know, you just confessed to
conspiracy to commit a crime. If I
were playing things by the book, I
could arrest you right here.
57:
But then I'd have to duke it out with
the backup you brought hiding
behind you, right?
60:
Just by the by, you guys know you're
the most heavily surveilled militant
organization in Palpebra, right?
64:
Militant organization? Is that how
the Guild sees us?!
69:
Yep. Probably because you go and
do stuff like this.
72:
You could have done this without
telling me. Why waste your breath?
77:
Because it seems you want to avoid
fighting the Vesta.
81:
Exactly. You made an effort to look
for another way to handle this
situation.
83:
It goes without saying, but... even if
you displace them, they'll still be
here, living among you.
86:
They're not likely to forget how they
were treated, either. You'll have a
ticking time bomb right in the
middle of Palpebra.
90: ...Not if we wipe them all out.
94:
But you can't. You won't. That's not
the type of place Palpebra is.
96:
You said it yourself—the Guild
Knights need more people. You're
even getting help from adventurers!
101:
*sigh* If it isn't our neighboring
kingdom's unpredictable actions, it's
dragons that come attacking from
out of nowhere. Can't catch a break.
103:
Meanwhile, my subordinates are
yapping at me to do something
about all the orphans in
town—rightfully so, mind you.
105:
In the middle of all that, we get giant
angel robots? This isn't the time to
be sowing the seeds of civil unrest.
Palpebra needs allies.
108:
If your enemy was right in front of
you, staring you in the face, you'd be
able to cooperate with us, right?
112: That's what I wanted to ask you.
115: Well, when you put it like that...
118:
So, you going to give me a time and
place, or what? I'll make sure to take
a well-timed stroll past there.
127: It's time. Open a path to the Rift!
130:
With that sword of yours, you should
be able to do it!
140: Why are you aiding our people?
143:
Are the people of this world not your
comrades?
146: I... have my reasons. My justifications.
149:
But... the truth is, I just couldn't
abandon you guys in your time of
need.
I hope that's good enough.
152: Stella did this once... Now it's my turn!
156:
What're you standing around all
flustered for? Go save your friends,
sheep lady.
170:
Wait... Haven't I seen this place
somewhere before—
173:
Alk! Don't go running off on your own
like that. You never know what could
jump out here!
177:
Speak of the devil.
The hell are these things?!
181:
They're Antibodies—constructs of
the Overlords, sent out to
exterminate those who try to cross
over to other worlds.
183:
They're much weaker than Purgers,
so don't worry. You shouldn't have
any trouble taking them down.
187: What, you ain't joining the fight?
191:
I think I'll pass. I'm like Stella,
remember? I'm not all that useful
when it comes to actual combat.
195: You sound almost proud of that.
198:
Whatever. Guess it's up to us, Alk!
Let's do this!
